Gazprom, Aksa to Bid for Turkish Gas Contract Sale, Vatan Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-06-02T06:11:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/gazprom-aksa-to-bid-for-turkish-gas-contract-sale-vatan-says.html
Aksa Enerji Uretim AS (AKSEN) , a Turkish
electricity producer, and  Gazprom OAO (GAZP)  signed an agreement to buy
wholesale gas import contracts from  Turkey ’s pipeline utility
Boru Hatlari Ile Tasima AS, or Botas,  Vatan  said, citing Aksa
Chairman Cemil Kazanci.  Botas will collect bids from investors until Sept. 8 in an
auction to sell a total of 6 billion cubic meters of gas that it
buys from Gazprom through a pipeline under the  Black Sea ,
Kazanci said, according to the newspaper.  Ankara-based Botas will sell the rights to import the gas
in lots of 250 million cubic meters per year, according to an
announcement in the government’s Official Gazette on May 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 